							<li>
    <strong>Tuesday</strong>
    <div class="item  ">
        <div class="img_w">
            <div>01</div>
            <img width="120" height="90" src="http://thedailyshow.mtvnimages.com/images/shows/tds/upcoming_guests/david_mitchell_v6.jpg?width=120&amp;height=90&amp;quality=0.91&amp;crop=true" alt="" />
                    </div>
        <h3>David Mitchell  </h3>
        <small>
            Author
        </small>
    </div>
            <div class="baseball-card">
    <div class="header"></div>
    <div class="middle">
        <h2>David Mitchell</h2>
        <div class="bc-content">
            <img width="160" height="120" src="http://thedailyshow.mtvnimages.com/images/shows/tds/upcoming_guests/david_mitchell_v6.jpg?width=160&amp;height=120&amp;quality=0.91&amp;crop=true" alt="" />
            David Mitchell is an award-winning British author. In a translation of the memoir "The Reason I Jump: The Inner Voice of a Thirteen-Year-Old Boy with Autism," (2013) which was written by a thirteen-year-old boy named Naoki Higashida, Mitchell describes how the enlightening book allowed him to better understand how his own autistic child experiences daily life. He and his wife, KA Yoshida, translated the book from the original Japanese. Mitchell's bestselling works of fiction include "Ghostwritten" (1999), "number9dream" (2001), and 2004's "Cloud Atlas," which was a finalist for the Man Booker Prize for Fiction. He also wrote "Black Swan Green" (2006) and "The Thousand Autumns of Jacob de Zoet" (2010). Born in England, Mitchell earned bachelor's degrees in English and American Literature before completing a Master's in Comparative Literature at the University of Kent. He lives in Ireland.
        </div>
                    <dl class="bc-related-news">
                <dt>Related Links:</dt>
                                                            <dd class="first">
                                                <a target="_blank" href="http://www.amazon.com/The-Reason-Jump-Thirteen-Year-Old-Autism/dp/0812994868">Buy "The Reason I Jump"</a></dd>
                                                            <dd>|
                                        <a target="_blank" href="http://www.amazon.com/David-Mitchell/e/B000APTQBE">Visit his Amazon author page</a></dd>
                                                            <dd>|
                                        <a target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/mitchell_book">Follow him on Twitter</a></dd>
                                                            <dd>|
                                        <a target="_blank" href="http://www.vanityfair.com/online/daily/2010/07/qa-with-david-mitchell-literary-platypus">Read his Vanity Fair interview</a></dd>
                            </dl> <!-- .bc-related-news -->
                    </div>
