							<li>
    <strong>Thursday</strong>
    <div class="item  ">
        <div class="img_w">
            <div>03</div>
            <img width="120" height="90" src="http://thedailyshow.mtvnimages.com/images/shows/tds/upcoming_guests/kerry_washington_v6.jpg?width=120&amp;height=90&amp;quality=0.91&amp;crop=true" alt="" />
                    </div>
        <h3>Kerry Washington  </h3>
        <small>
            Actor
        </small>
    </div>
            <div class="baseball-card">
    <div class="header"></div>
    <div class="middle">
        <h2>Kerry Washington</h2>
        <div class="bc-content">
            <img width="160" height="120" src="http://thedailyshow.mtvnimages.com/images/shows/tds/upcoming_guests/kerry_washington_v6.jpg?width=160&amp;height=120&amp;quality=0.91&amp;crop=true" alt="" />
            Kerry Washington is an American film and television actress who currently stars as Olivia Pope on the ABC drama series "Scandal." Starting in 2000, Washington began earning roles in movies such as "Ray" (2004), "Mr. & Mrs. Smith" (2005), "Fantastic Four" (2005) and "The Last King of Scotland" (2006). In 2012, she played "Broomhilda von Shaft" alongside Jamie Foxx in Quentin Tarantino's "Django Unchained." Her TV credits include a recurring role on "Boston Legal" and in the mini-series "Black Panther" (2010). She received her first Primetime Emmy nomination for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series for her work on "Scandal" in 2013.
        </div>
