		</div>
		<h3>Robin Williams</h3>
		<small>Academy Award-winning Actor, Comedian</small>
	</div>
	<i></i>
	<div class="baseball-card">
    <div class="header"></div>
    <div class="middle">
        <h2>Robin Williams</h2>
        <div class="bc-content">
            <img width="160" height="120" src="http://thedailyshow.mtvnimages.com/images/shows/tds/videos/season_18/18158/ds_18158_04.jpg?width=160&amp;height=120&amp;quality=0.91&amp;crop=true" alt="" />
            Comedian and actor Robin Williams rose to fame as the alien Mork in the 1978 TV series "Mork and Mindy." His latest project is the new TV comedy "The Crazy Ones." He has performed in many movies and won an Academy Award for his performance in 1997's "Good Will Hunting." Williams has also won two Emmy Awards, four Golden Globe Awards, two Screen Actors Guild Awards and five Grammy Awards for his work, and his performances in the movies "The Dead Poets Society" and "Good Morning, Vietnam" were all nominated for Academy Awards. Williams has done many stand-up comedy tours since the early 70s, including 1986's "Robin Williams: At The Met" and 2008's "Weapons of Self Destruction." Williams is also famous for his charity work, including performing in Comic Relief to raise money for the homeless.
        </div>
