		<h3>Atoms for Peace</h3>
		<small>Band</small>
	</div>
	<i></i>
	<div class="baseball-card">
    <div class="header"></div>
    <div class="middle">
        <h2>Atoms for Peace</h2>
        <div class="bc-content">
            <img width="160" height="120" src="http://thedailyshow.mtvnimages.com/images/shows/tds/videos/season_18/18157/ds_18157_03.jpg?width=160&amp;height=120&amp;quality=0.91&amp;crop=true" alt="" />
            Atoms for Peace is an experimental rock band headed by Radiohead frontman Thom Yorke. The group is a collaboration that includes a number of very accomplished musicians, including Red Hot Chili Peppers bassist Flea, Radiohead producer Nigel Godrich, Joey Waronker of Beck and R.E.M., and Mauro Refosco. The group's 2013 debut album is "Amok".
        </div>
