		</div>
		<h3>Richard Dawkins</h3>
		<small>Evolutionary Biologist, Author</small>
	</div>
	<i></i>
	<div class="baseball-card">
    <div class="header"></div>
    <div class="middle">
        <h2>Richard Dawkins</h2>
        <div class="bc-content">
            <img width="160" height="120" src="http://thedailyshow.mtvnimages.com/images/shows/tds/videos/season_18/18156/ds_18156_05.jpg?width=160&amp;height=120&amp;quality=0.91&amp;crop=true" alt="" />
            Richard Dawkins is one of the world's leading experts in evolutionary biology, an acclaimed author, and a prominent atheist. He has written and spoken widely on the subject of evolution and in support of his criticism of intelligent design and the existence of God. His books include "The Selfish Gene" (1976), "River Out of Eden: A Darwinian View of Life" (1995), "Unweaving the Rainbow" (1997), "The Ancestor's Tale" (2004) and "The God Delusion" (2006). Dawkins earned his doctorate at the University of California, Berkeley, where he studied under Nobel Prize winner Niko Tinbergen. Among his numerous awards and distinctions, from 1995 until 2008, Dawkins held the Charles Simonyi Chair of Public Understanding of Science at Oxford University. He is currently an emeritus fellow of New College, Oxford. His new memoir is "An Appetite for Wonder."
        </div>
                    <dl class="bc-related-news">
                <dt>Related Links:</dt>
                                                            <dd class="first">
