		</div>
		<h3>Chelsea Clinton</h3>
		<small>Vice Chair of the Clinton Foundation</small>
	</div>
	<i></i>
	<div class="baseball-card">
    <div class="header"></div>
    <div class="middle">
        <h2>Chelsea Clinton</h2>
        <div class="bc-content">
            <img width="160" height="120" src="http://thedailyshow.mtvnimages.com/images/shows/tds/videos/season_18/18155/ds_18155_04.jpg?width=160&amp;height=120&amp;quality=0.91&amp;crop=true" alt="" />
            Chelsea Clinton serves as Vice Chair of the Clinton Foundation, which is led by her parents, President Bill Clinton and Secretary Hillary Rodham Clinton. The Clinton Foundation aims to create partnerships between governments, NGOs, and businesses to address global challenges with a focus on economic development, climate change, global health, and health and wellness. Clinton focuses her efforts on improving the developing world's access to health care through the Clinton Health Access Initiative, plus a variety of other programs including the Clinton Health Matters Initiative and the Millennium Network. In addition to serving on numerous non-profit boards, Clinton contributes to NBC News as a special correspondent. Clinton attended Stanford University, went on to earn a Master's degree from both Oxford and Columbia University's Mailman School of Public Health, and she is currently pursuing a doctorate at Oxford. She lives in New York City with her husband, Marc Mezvinsky.
        </div>
