		<h3>Jake Gyllenhaal</h3>
		<small>Actor</small>
	</div>
	<i></i>
	<div class="baseball-card">
    <div class="header"></div>
    <div class="middle">
        <h2>Jake Gyllenhaal</h2>
        <div class="bc-content">
            <img width="160" height="120" src="http://thedailyshow.mtvnimages.com/images/shows/tds/videos/season_16/16043/ds_16043_04_16x9.jpg?width=160&amp;height=120&amp;quality=0.91&amp;crop=true" alt="" />
            Jake Gyllenhaal is an Oscar-nominated actor. His latest movie is "Prisoners" (2013). Gyllenhaal's career took off on the heels of the cult hit "Donnie Darko" (2001). Since then, Gyllenhaal has appeared in many films, including 2002's "Lovely & Amazing," 2004's "The Day After Tomorrow," 2007's "Zodiac," and 2011's "Source Code." In 2005, he received an Academy Award nomination for Best Supporting Actor for his work in Ang Lee's hugely successful romantic drama, "Brokeback Mountain." The son of film director Stephen Gyllenhaal and screenwriter Naomi Foner Gyllenhaal, he is a politically active Democrat and, like his sister and parents, has campaigned for causes such as Rock the Vote, environmental issues and the American Civil Liberties Union.
        </div>
