		<h3>Billy Crystal</h3>
		<small>Comedian</small>
	</div>
	<i></i>
	<div class="baseball-card">
    <div class="header"></div>
    <div class="middle">
        <h2>Billy Crystal</h2>
        <div class="bc-content">
            <img width="160" height="120" src="http://thedailyshow.mtvnimages.com/images/shows/tds/videos/season_16/16045/ds_16045_04_16x9.jpg?width=160&amp;height=120&amp;quality=0.91&amp;crop=true" alt="" />
            Billy Crystal started doing stand-up comedy when he was 16. Decades later, his long list of career achievements as an entertainer, actor, writer, and director includes "When Harry Met Sally..." (1989), "City Slickers" (1991), "Analyze This" (1999), five-time host of the Academy Awards, plus multiple Emmy Award wins. Billy Crystal's latest project is his new memoir, "Still Foolin' 'Em: Where I've Been, Where I'm Going, and Where the Hell Are My Keys?"
        </div>
                    <dl class="bc-related-news">
